      • findMultiWord

        public static int findMultiWord(java.util.List<CoreLabel> tokens,
                                int startIndex,
                                java.util.List<java.lang.String> synset,
                                java.lang.StringBuffer multiWordToken)
        Find the synset for a multi-word string, if it exists.
        Parameters:
        tokens - is a List of CoreLabel words.
        startIndex - is the first word in the list to look at, note that token numbers start at 1 but list inices start at 0
        synset - is an array of only one element, if a synset is found and empty otherwise
        Returns:
        the index into the next word to be checked, in text, which could be the same as startIndex, if no multi-word was found
